description: The notification represents that a rogue AP or a station was
detected by WIDS.
The NMS would refer to MIB table under hpnicfDot11WIDSDetectGroup
group to get more detailed information.
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSDetectRogueTrap HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSRogueMAC s EXAMPL HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSRogueType i 1 HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSMonitorMAC s EXAMPL HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11MonitorAPID s EXAMPLE HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11MonitorApRadioID i 9999

description: Represents which rogue AP or station.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSRogueMAC

description: Represents the rogue type.
The following value are supported
rogueAp(1) - A rogue AP
rogueStation(2) - A rogue Station
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSRogueType

description: Represents which monitor detected the rogue AP or station.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSMonitorMAC

description: Represents monitor AP's APID.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11MonitorAPID

description: Represents monitor AP's radio ID
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11MonitorApRadioID

description: The notification represents a rogue Ad hoc station was detected.
Represents the MAC address of Ad hoc station.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSAdHocMAC

description: Represents which monitor detected the rogue AP or station.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSMonitorMAC

description: The notification represents which unauthorized SSID are
accessed in the network.
The notification will be sent to NMS when an
unauthorized SSID is detected on the network for the
first time.

event.Summary: Unauthorized SSID $v1 accessed in the network

objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSUnauthorSSIDTrap HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11UnauthorSSIDName s EXAMPLE HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSMonitorMAC s EXAMPL HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11MonitorAPID s EXAMPLE HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11MonitorApRadioID i 9999

description: Represents an unauthorized SSID.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11UnauthorSSIDName

description: Represents which monitor detected the rogue AP or station.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSMonitorMAC

description: Represents monitor AP's APID.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11MonitorAPID

description: Represents monitor AP's radio ID
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11MonitorApRadioID

description: The notification represents that a rogue device has aged out
and moved to history table or the device type has been changed
to friendly.
The notification will be sent to NMS whenever a rogue disappears.
Represents which rogue AP or station.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSRogueMAC

description: This notification occurs when some type of attack is detected.
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSDetectAttack HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSAtkHisType i 1 HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSAtkHisChl i 9999 HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSAtkHisDctTime s EXAMPLEE HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSAtkHisAPName s EXAMPLE

description: Represents the channel in which the attack was detected.

description: Represents the time at which this attack was detected.
variables.name: HPN-ICF-DOT11-WIDS-MIB::hpnicfDot11WIDSAtkHisDctTime

description: Represents the name of the AP which detected this attack.
